      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BUSTER BIFF (3) won nicely two back when straight out to the mile before a narrow defeat last start at Bunbury. This is tougher, though he's open to further improvement and Nottle's claim comes in handy. Has the scope to improve further with the rise in trip. SAVORSKI (4) missed over 2200m here a fortnight ago when beaten by an outsider of the race. The improvement he showed was good though and the better draw this time can see him sit closer. Can go one better here without surprising. ETERNAL ROMANCE (7) finished off strongly over the 2200m journey last time out and this looks to shape similarly. The wide draw is the query, but if he gets the tempo to suit, then he'll be finishing strongly. WHISKERS HARBOUR (2) will appreciate getting out in trip today and can make an impression. ASARKA (8) won't be far away.",
